.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-NOTEBOOK" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.47" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-notebook \- Launch a tracked JupyterLab or VS Code notebook server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose notebook [OPTIONS] [ARGS]...
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Submit a long\-running, tracked interactive server (JupyterLab or VS Code `code tunnel`) as a single\-service Slurm job, wait for it to become ready, and print the connection URL. Use \-\-local to run on the current host through the local supervisor. Manage the session with `hpc\-compose status` and stop it with `hpc\-compose cancel`.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--kind\fR \fIKIND\fR
Interactive server preset. Default: jupyter. Possible values: jupyter, vscode.
.TP
\fB--image\fR \fIIMAGE\fR
Container image override (required for \-\-kind vscode).
.TP
\fB--port\fR \fIPORT\fR
Jupyter port (ignored for \-\-kind vscode). Default: 8888.
.TP
\fB--token\fR \fITOKEN\fR
Jupyter auth token; a random token is generated when omitted.
.TP
\fB--volume\fR \fIHOST:CONTAINER\fR
Additional host:container mount; may be passed multiple times.
.TP
\fB--working\-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR
Container working directory.
.TP
\fB--tunnel\-name\fR \fINAME\fR
VS Code tunnel name. Default: hpc\-compose.
.TP
\fB--ready\-timeout\fR \fIDURATION\fR
Give up waiting for the notebook to become ready after this duration. Default: 10m.
.TP
\fB--follow\fR
Stream service logs after readiness instead of detaching.
.TP
\fB--dry\-run\fR
Render the launcher script without submitting.
.TP
\fIARGS\fR
Extra argv forwarded to the server command after \-\-.
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--enroot\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the enroot executable. Default: enroot.
.TP
\fB--apptainer\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the apptainer executable. Default: apptainer.
.TP
\fB--singularity\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the singularity executable. Default: singularity.
.TP
\fB--keep\-failed\-prep\fR
Keep failed preparation state on disk for later inspection.
.TP
\fB--skip\-prepare\fR
Skip image import and prepare reuse checks.
.TP
\fB--force\-rebuild\fR
Refresh imported and prepared artifacts before running.
.TP
\fB--no\-preflight\fR
Skip the preflight phase before running.
.TP
\fB--resources\fR \fINAME\fR
Settings resource profile to apply.
.TP
\fB--time\fR \fITIME\fR
Slurm time limit.
.TP
\fB--mem\fR \fIMEM\fR
Slurm memory request.
.TP
\fB--cpus\-per\-task\fR \fIN\fR
Slurm CPUs per task.
.TP
\fB--gpus\fR \fIN\fR
Slurm GPU count.
.TP
\fB--partition\fR \fIPARTITION\fR
Slurm partition.
.TP
\fB--env\fR \fIKEY=VALUE\fR
Environment variable to pass into the notebook container.
.TP
\fB--local\fR
Run on the current host through the local Pyxis\-compatible launcher.
.TP
\fB--script\-out\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR
Write the rendered launcher script to this path.
.TP
\fB--sbatch\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sbatch executable. Default: sbatch.
.TP
\fB--srun\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the srun executable. Default: srun.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
